  "business_context": "SMS records capture text-message touchpoints — a channel that has grown rapidly in CRM workflows for appointment reminders, payment confirmations, donor stewardship outreach, two-factor authentication flows, and increasingly for sales / fundraising conversations. Compared to email, text messages are short (typically 160-1600 characters), have higher open rates (95%+ within minutes), and require explicit opt-in consent under TCPA in the US. Consent management is the most distinctive operational concern: sending a text to a contact who hasn't opted in carries legal liability. Modeling varies: HubSpot has Communication as a generic Engagement type that includes SMS (Communication subtypes include SMS, WhatsApp, LinkedIn); Bloomerang has Interaction subtype=Text Message; Salesforce has limited native SMS — Marketing Cloud's MobileConnect handles bulk SMS via separate data model, while Service Cloud's Messaging covers conversational SMS; EspoCRM and CiviCRM lack native SMS entities. Twilio integrations drive most SMS implementations across systems. When interviewing clients, surface \"SMS\" by asking whether they need to track text- message communication, whether they have TCPA-compliant opt-in workflows, and whether SMS interactions need to be threaded with other channels in a unified contact timeline.",
  "catalog_id": "activity-sms",
